   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>"(L.4) . . . (I will deliver it free and clear from) all public taxes and imposts . . . and requisition and contributions up to the sixth year and including the past sixth year itself, because the revenues from it belong to you who purchase in cession. And to you belong the taxes accruing from the same present seventh year. This sale and cession, written in Ammonius' own hand and written in triplicate, is valid wherever it is presented and for whoever presents it on your behalf. And whenever you choose, I will publish it for you. Seventh year of Emperors Caesares Lucius Septimius Severus Pius Pertinax Arabicus Adiabenicus Parthicus Maximus and Marcus Aurelius Antoninus Augusti, Pharmouthi 13 (?).</ab>
         </div>
